  "body": {
    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"NeonSign_Banner.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/638877713/NeonSign_Banner.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762010400160&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=427\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/638877713/NeonSign_Banner.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762010400160&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"1080\" data-width=\"1920\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"638877781\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"NeonSign_Banner.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"638877713\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"6\" data-media-id=\"ec2e9edd-f89d-4379-b3c3-0e08b00268a6\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/638877713/NeonSign_Banner.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762010400160&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1520&amp;height=854 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/638877713/NeonSign_Banner.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762010400160&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=427 1x\"></span><p /><p>Leading on from the previous lesson, let’s now bring our neon sign to life with some cool VEX code in Solaris!</p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://downloads.renderman.pixar.com/RU/Resources/USD/NeonR.zip\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-left\" alt=\"DownloadButton2.png\" width=\"158\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/638877713/DownloadButton2.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762010399314&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=158&amp;height=37\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/638877713/DownloadButton2.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762010399314&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"68\" data-width=\"286\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"638877751\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"DownloadButton2.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"638877713\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"6\" data-media-id=\"995f31c5-f337-49f0-a079-d87895da9dfb\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/638877713/DownloadButton2.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762010399314&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=286&amp;height=68 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/638877713/DownloadButton2.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762010399314&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=158&amp;height=37 1x\"></span></a><p>In this lesson, we’re going to amend the four Glow shaders from the <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RU/pages/392953857/Neons\" data-linked-resource-id=\"392953857\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Neons </a>lesson to be able to control the PxrSurface Glow Intensity with a Primvar.  Once done, we’ll be able to control the neons' animation using some clever VEX code.</p><p /><div class=\"panel conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"402da4ac-ee20-452f-960d-557aea2b22f2\" data-macro-name=\"panel\" style=\"background-color: #4C9AFF;border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"panelContent\" style=\"background-color: #4C9AFF;\">\n<p><strong><span class=\"legacy-color-text-inverse\">USD Asset Setup</span></strong></p>\n</div></div><p>What we’re after is to dynamically control the ‘chasing’ animation of the neon tubes.  </p><p /><p>The first thing we need to do is edit the Glow shaders.  In Solaris, this can be done by creating a <em>editmaterialproperties</em> node.  We can add the glow shader to this node and further edit it.  </p><p>Inside the first Glow Shader, let’s create a PrimVar node, leave the Variable type to Float, but make sure you set the Float value to 0.1. This gives us an initial intensity value.  </p><p>In this example, or PrimVar is called Outer_INT</p><p>The resultR from the Primvar is then connected to the glowgain of the PxrSurface.</p><p /><p>We need to repeat these steps for each of the other Glow shaders, ensuring each PrimVar has a unique name. </p><p>I used </p><p>Outer_INT<br/>Mid_INT</p><p>Inner_INT</p><p>White_INT</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Solaris_Animate_Solaris_AddPrimvar.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/638877713/Solaris_Animate_Solaris_AddPrimvar.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762010873573&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=213\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/638877713/Solaris_Animate_Solaris_AddPrimvar.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762010873573&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"404\" data-width=\"1435\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"638615916\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"Solaris_Animate_Solaris_AddPrimvar.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"638877713\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"6\" data-media-id=\"ac946a5f-a09e-4840-81d3-84614072b416\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/638877713/Solaris_Animate_Solaris_AddPrimvar.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762010873573&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1435&amp;height=404 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/638877713/Solaris_Animate_Solaris_AddPrimvar.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762010873573&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=213 1x\"></span><p>Once done, we need to re-publish the USD asset and then reload it into our main network.</p><p /><div class=\"panel conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"a48239e7-1bdb-4d39-90e5-5c5803fbcaf4\" data-macro-name=\"panel\" style=\"background-color: #4C9AFF;border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"panelContent\" style=\"background-color: #4C9AFF;\">\n<p><strong><span class=\"legacy-color-text-inverse\">Time to Animate!</span></strong></p>\n</div></div><p>Hand-animating these neons would take a while, but why do it by hand when we have the power of VEX in Solaris?</p><p>Start by creating an AttributeWrangle node and paste the following code into the VEXpression box.</p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"5fe65425-f8b1-4337-bf58-52e3a9af3e4f\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">int off = chi(&quot;off&quot;);\nint on = chi(&quot;on&quot;);\nint transition = chi(&quot;transition&quot;);\nint A = off;\nint B = off + transition;\nint C = off + transition + on;\nint D = off + 2 * transition + on;\n\nfloat val = 0;\nint frame = int(@Frame - $FSTART + chi(&quot;frameOffset&quot;) * @elemnum) % (D + 1);\n\nif(frame &lt; A)\n    val = 0;\nelse if (frame &gt;= A &amp;&amp; frame &lt; B)\n    val = 1 - (B - frame) / float(B - A);\nelse if(frame &gt;= B &amp;&amp; frame &lt; C)\n    val = 1;\nelse if (frame &gt;= C &amp;&amp; frame &lt; D)\n    val = (D - frame) / float(D - C);\nval *= ch(&quot;intensity&quot;);\n\n@inputs:defaultFloat = val;\n//@inputs:intensity = val;</pre>\n</div></div><p /><p>Once compiled, you’ll see the following interface!</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Solaris_Animate_Solaris_VEX.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/638877713/Solaris_Animate_Solaris_VEX.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762011438583&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=730\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/638877713/Solaris_Animate_Solaris_VEX.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762011438583&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"905\" data-width=\"941\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"638779776\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"Solaris_Animate_Solaris_VEX.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"638877713\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"6\" data-media-id=\"867aa90a-5e60-4bca-9ece-32eb298fe16c\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/638877713/Solaris_Animate_Solaris_VEX.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762011438583&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=941&amp;height=905 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/638877713/Solaris_Animate_Solaris_VEX.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762011438583&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=730 1x\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Solaris_Animate_Solaris_1.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/638877713/Solaris_Animate_Solaris_1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762011901514&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=384\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/638877713/Solaris_Animate_Solaris_1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762011901514&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"1293\" data-width=\"2557\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"639139908\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"Solaris_Animate_Solaris_1.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"638877713\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"6\" data-media-id=\"b10a26ab-2b0f-45fd-9891-aa10b28acf20\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/638877713/Solaris_Animate_Solaris_1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762011901514&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1520&amp;height=768 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/638877713/Solaris_Animate_Solaris_1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762011901514&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=384 1x\"></span><p>The last thing we need to do is to specify which Primitives we want to run the code over.</p><p /><p>Using a handy wildcard as </p><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"c10ad039-b5c4-48d1-b8ae-fb07e18e79e3\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">/NeonR/materials/**/**_INT</pre>\n</div></div><p>will look through all the materials and find the nodes that have _INT in the same.  We can easily and quickly pick up all the primvars we have in our Glow Shaders.</p><p /><p>Here is a quick rundown of the parameters </p><p><strong>OFF</strong></p><p>How many frames does each neon stay OFF for</p><p><strong>ON</strong></p><p>How many frames does the neons stay ON for</p><p><strong>Transition</strong></p><p>The number of frames to ramp up and down</p><p><strong>FrameOffset</strong></p><p>Change this value to alter the offset time between all the neons</p><p><strong>Intensity</strong></p><p>What is the maximum intensity the neons should reach</p><p /><p>And that’s it… Feel free to play with the parameters to create your own chasing times, and you can use this code on all your neons, too.  </p><p>Just make sure you have a PrimVar attached to the <em>glowgain in </em>your surfaces, and you’ll be good to go.</p><p /><div class=\"panel conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"\" data-macro-name=\"panel\" style=\"background-color: #EAE6FF;border-color: #998DD9;border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"panelContent\" style=\"background-color: #EAE6FF;\">\n<p>Thanks to Damien Maupu at Pixar for the cool VFX code!</p>\n</div></div><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p />"
    }
  },
